name: "Three Finches" Etching
description:
This is a dry point etching of three zebra finches, a native bird of Australia. 

The image is scratched into an acetate plate which is then inked up with a thick sticky ink. The ink is wiped back so it only remains in the scratched lines. I add colour by a technique known as a la poupee. This means the colours are added to the plate and blended in. The plate is then put onto my printing press and pulled through with dampened paper on top. This whole inking up process has to be repeated for each subsequent print. Due to the hand made nature of printmaking each print is slightly different, hence the term "original print."

This print is part of my current collection for my recent exhibition in Falkner Gallery, Castlemaine, Victoria, Australia.

Measurements
Image size 13 x 13.5cm (5 1/8 x 5 5/16 inches)
Paper size 26 x 27 cm (10 1/4 x 10 5/8 inches)

Printed on highest quality Hahnemuhle cotton rag paper

name: "Blue Wren" Dry Point Etching
description:
This is an original etching of an Australian native bird called a superb fairy wren, also known as a blue wren.

The fairy wrens in Australia are just gorgeous, displaying vivid blue plumage on the males. Sometimes they are known blue wrens and the different varieties have great names such as Lovely Fairy Wren and Splendid Fairy Wren, this one is a Superb Fairy Wren. They sort of dance around, hopping just a short distance from you in pairs, looking for small insects.

This is a dry point etching inked up in a vivid dark blue and printed onto highest quality Hahnemuhle cotton rag printmaking paper. It is one in an edition of 30. If you would like to see my work in person you can view it in a number of galleries around Melbourne or if you live near Daylesford, Victoria, you can arrange to visit my studio in the woods!
